**Technologies and Skills Used**: Autodesk Fusion, NASA CEA, ANSYS Mechanical, ANSYS Fluent, Lathe & Mill

I designed an augmented spark igniter (ASI), a miniature rocket engine used to ignite a larger rocket engine using liquid bipropellants. The ASI was designed to ignite a pressure-fed liquid bipropellant engine operating at a chamber pressure of 600 psi. This is a high pressure environment, which was a challenging situation when designing this ASI. I modeled the ASI in ANSYS to examine its thermal and structural properties. I also modeled the nozzle flow using ANSYS Fluent. I am currently machining and assembling the ASI. 

